creator: Dropbox, Inc.
descriptionHtml:
Dropbox lets anyone upload and transfer files to the cloud, and share them with anyone. Back up photos, videos, docs, and other files to cloud storage, and access files synced with any of your computers or mobile devices—from anywhere. And with advanced sharing features, it’s easy to send files—large or small—to friends, family, and co-workers.

Features:
• Automatically upload the photos and videos in your camera roll to cloud storage—all in the background.
• Access any file in your account—even offline—and preview over 175 file types, no special software required.
• Easily send large files by copying and pasting a link you can give to anyone, even if they don’t have a Dropbox account.
• Scan documents to cloud photo storage using your camera, and turn receipts, documents, whiteboards, and notes into PDFs.

Sign up now for your free Dropbox Plus trial. You’ll get 2 TB (2,000 GB) of storage—that’s enough room to save files from all your linked devices. And Dropbox Smart Sync technology can move out-of-date files off your hard drive and to the cloud. You’ll also be able to roll back unwanted changes to any folder, or your entire Dropbox, up to 30 days.

Or, existing Plus customers can upgrade to Dropbox Professional. With 3 TB (3,000GB), you can store all your stuff—from work projects to personal photos—and have space to spare. You and your clients can comment on most file types without leaving Dropbox. And you can protect your work with a watermark, add shared link controls, or rewind your account up to 180 days.

Before completing payment, you’ll see the plan price. This amount will be charged to your Google Play account and will vary by plan and country. Dropbox subscriptions purchased in app renew monthly or yearly, depending on your plan. To avoid auto-renewal, turn it off in at least 24 hours before your subscription renews. You can turn off auto-renewal anytime time from your Google Play account settings.

We’d love to hear from you! Join the Dropbox community: https://www.dropboxforum.com
Terms of Service: https://www.dropbox.com/terms
Privacy Policy: https://www.dropbox.com/privacy
descriptionShort: Cloud storage & more - backup, access and share all your docs, photos and files.

descriptionHtml:
Dropbox lets anyone upload and transfer files to the cloud, and share them with anyone. Back up and sync docs, photos, videos, and other files to cloud storage and access them from any device, no matter where you are. And with advanced sharing features, it’s easy to share docs and send files—large or small—to family, friends, and co-workers.

Features:
• Automatically upload videos and photos from your camera roll to cloud photo storage—all in the background—for easy video sharing and photo sharing.
• Access any file in your account—even offline—and preview over 175 different file types with no special software required.
• Easily send large files by copying and pasting a link you can give to anyone, even if they don’t have a Dropbox account.
• Scan documents, receipts, IDs, photos, and more using your mobile device and transform them into high-quality PDFs, so you can view and send anywhere.
• Sync folders on your PC or Mac to Dropbox with computer backup, and recover older versions or restore deleted files with version history and file recovery.

Sign up now for your free Dropbox Plus trial. You’ll get 2 TB (2,000 GB) of storage space—that’s enough room to save files from all your linked devices. We’ve also introduced some new features as part of your Plus plan: Dropbox Passwords to store and sync passwords across all your devices and Dropbox Vault to secure and organize your most sensitive documents. And with Dropbox Rewind, you can roll back any file, folder, or your entire account, up to 30 days.

Existing Plus customers can upgrade to Dropbox Professional. With 3 TB (3,000GB), you can store all your stuff—from work projects to personal photos—and have space to spare. You and your clients can comment on most file types without leaving Dropbox. And you can protect your work with a watermark, add shared link controls, or rewind your account up to 180 days.

Before completing payment, you’ll see the plan price. This amount will be charged to your Google Play account and will vary by plan and country. Dropbox subscriptions purchased in app renew monthly or yearly, depending on your plan. To avoid auto-renewal, turn it off in at least 24 hours before your subscription renews. You can turn off auto-renewal anytime time from your Google Play account settings.

Dropbox is a secure cloud solutions leader trusted by Fortune 500 companies for their most sensitive data. Over 14 million paid users choose Dropbox because they know they can count on a company that’s also dedicated to their security and privacy—no matter what they do or where they are. Let Dropbox be your all-in-one file storage, file organizer, file transfer, and file sharing solution for all your devices—from Android to iPhone and Mac to PC.

Dropbox lets anyone upload and transfer files to the cloud, and share them with anyone. Back up and sync docs, photos, videos, and other files to cloud storage and access them from any device, no matter where you are. And with advanced sharing features, it’s easy to share docs and send files—large or small—to family, friends, and co-workers.

Features:
• Automatically upload videos and photos from your camera roll to cloud photo storage—all in the background—for easy video sharing and photo sharing.
• Access any file in your account—even offline—and preview over 175 different file types with no special software required.
• Easily send large files by copying and pasting a link you can give to anyone, even if they don’t have a Dropbox account.
• Scan documents, receipts, IDs, photos, and more using your mobile device and transform them into high-quality PDFs, so you can view and send anywhere.
• Sync folders on your PC or Mac to Dropbox with computer backup, and recover older versions or restore deleted files with version history and file recovery.

Sign up now for your free Dropbox Plus trial. You’ll get 2 TB (2,000 GB) of storage space—that’s enough room to save files from all your linked devices. We’ve also introduced some new features as part of your Plus plan: Dropbox Passwords to store and sync passwords across all your devices and Dropbox Vault to secure and organize your most sensitive documents. And with Dropbox Rewind, you can roll back any file, folder, or your entire account, up to 30 days.

Existing Plus customers can upgrade to Dropbox Professional. With 3 TB (3,000GB), you can store all your stuff—from work projects to personal photos—and have space to spare. You and your clients can comment on most file types without leaving Dropbox. And you can protect your work with a watermark, add shared link controls, or rewind your account up to 180 days.

Before completing payment, you’ll see the plan price. This amount will be charged to your Google Play account and will vary by plan and country. Dropbox subscriptions purchased in app renew monthly or yearly, depending on your plan. To avoid auto-renewal, turn it off in at least 24 hours before your subscription renews. You can turn off auto-renewal anytime time from your Google Play account settings.

Dropbox is a secure cloud solutions leader trusted by Fortune 500 companies for their most sensitive data. Over 14 million paid users choose Dropbox because they know they can count on a company that’s also dedicated to their security and privacy—no matter what they do or where they are. Let Dropbox be your all-in-one file storage, file organizer, file transfer, and file sharing solution for all your devices—from Android to iPhone and Mac to PC.

We’d love to hear from you! Join the Dropbox community: https://www.dropboxforum.com
Terms of Service: https://www.dropbox.com/terms
Privacy Policy: https://www.dropbox.com/privacy

descriptionHtml:

Back up and sync photos, docs, videos, and other files to cloud storage drive and access them from any device, no matter where you are. And with advanced sharing features, it’s easy to share docs and send files—large or small—to family, friends, and co-workers through Dropbox’s cloud drive.

Features:
• Photo vault: automatically store videos, photos and docs from your camera roll to cloud photo storage, to backup your albums and for easy and secure video sharing and photo sharing.
• File organizer and manager: access any file or document in your account—even offline—and preview over 175 different file types with no special software required.
• Photo transfer app: send anywhere - easily transfer send large files and docs from your storage app by copying and pasting a link you can give to anyone, even if they don’t have a Dropbox account.
• Document Scanner: access an easy-to-use pdf scanner, and scan *documents using your mobile device and transform them into high-quality PDFs, so you can view, sign and send anywhere.
(*documents = receipts, IDs, photos, and more)
• Sync folders on your PC or Mac to Dropbox with cloud backup, and recover older versions or restore deleted files with version history and file recovery.

A cloud storage & drive app gives you extra space to backup, upload and share, scan and transfer files to the cloud, automatically. An easy backup and sync vault with safe access to your private or shared files. Today you can easily manage and share family albums, video albums and more.

Sign up now for your free Dropbox Plus trial. You’ll get 2 TB (2,000 GB) of storage space—that’s enough room to save files from all your linked devices. We’ve also introduced some new features as part of your Plus plan: Dropbox Passwords to store and sync passwords across all your devices and Dropbox Vault to secure and organize your most sensitive documents. And with Dropbox Rewind, you can roll back any file, folder, or your entire account, up to 30 days.

Existing Plus customers can upgrade to Dropbox Professional. With 3 TB (3,000GB), you can store all your stuff—from work projects to personal photos—and have space to spare. Before completing payment, you’ll see the plan price. This amount will be charged to your Google Play account and will vary by plan and country. Features:
• Photo vault: automatically store videos, photos and docs from your camera roll to cloud photo storage, to backup your albums and for easy and secure video sharing and photo sharing.
• File organizer and manager: access any file or document in your account—even offline—and preview over 175 different file types with no special software required.
• Photo transfer app: send anywhere - easily transfer send large files and docs from your storage app by copying and pasting a link you can give to anyone, even if they don’t have a Dropbox account.

Dropbox’s Cloud Drive lets anyone upload and transfer photos, documents and files to the cloud, and share them with anyone. Back up and sync photos, docs, videos, and other files to cloud storage drive and access them from any device, no matter where you are. And with advanced sharing features, it’s easy to share docs and send files—large or small—to family, friends, and co-workers through Dropbox’s cloud drive.

Features:
• Photo vault - automatically store videos , photos and docs from your camera roll to cloud photo storage, to backup your albums and for easy and secure video sharing and photo sharing.
• File organizer and manager - access any file or document in your account—even offline—and preview over 175 different file types with no special software required.
• Photo transfer app: send anywhere - easily transfer send large files and docs from your storage app by copying and pasting a link you can give to anyone, even if they don’t have a Dropbox account.
• Document Scanner - access an easy-to-use pdf scanner, and scan *documents using your mobile device and transform them into high-quality PDFs, so you can view, sign and send anywhere.
(*documents = receipts, IDs, photos, and more)
• Sync folders on your PC or Mac to Dropbox with cloud backup, and recover older versions or restore deleted files with version history and file recovery.

A cloud storage & drive app gives you extra space to backup, upload and share, scan and transfer files to the cloud, automatically. An easy backup and sync vault with safe access to your private or shared files. Today you can easily manage and share family albums, video albums and more.

Sign up now for your free Dropbox Plus trial. You’ll get 2 TB (2,000 GB) of storage space—that’s enough room to save files from all your linked devices. We’ve also introduced some new features as part of your Plus plan: Dropbox Passwords to store and sync passwords across all your devices and Dropbox Vault to secure and organize your most sensitive documents. And with Dropbox Rewind, you can roll back any file, folder, or your entire account, up to 30 days.

Existing Plus customers can upgrade to Dropbox Professional. With 3 TB (3,000GB), you can store all your stuff—from work projects to personal photos—and have space to spare. You and your clients can comment on most file types without leaving Dropbox. And you can protect your work with a watermark, add shared link controls, or rewind your account up to 180 days.

Before completing payment, you’ll see the plan price. This amount will be charged to your Google Play account and will vary by plan and country. Dropbox subscriptions purchased in app renew monthly or yearly, depending on your plan. To avoid auto-renewal, turn it off in at least 24 hours before your subscription renews. You can turn off auto-renewal anytime from your Google Play account settings.

Dropbox is a secure cloud solutions leader trusted by Fortune 500 companies for their most sensitive data. Over 14 million paid users choose Dropbox because they know they can count on a company that’s also dedicated to their security and privacy—no matter what they do or where they are. Let Dropbox be your all-in-one file storage, file organizer, file transfer, and file sharing solution for all your devices—from Android to iPhone and Mac to PC.

Dropbox is not affiliated with Amazon, Apple, Samsung, iCloud or Microsoft OneDrive.


We’d love to hear from you! Join the Dropbox community: https://www.dropboxforum.com
Terms of Service: https://www.dropbox.com/terms
Privacy Policy: https://www.dropbox.com/privacy

descriptionHtml:
Dropbox’s Cloud Drive lets anyone upload and transfer photos, documents and files to the cloud, and share them with anyone. Back up and sync photos, docs, videos, and other files to cloud storage drive and access them from any device, no matter where you are. And with advanced sharing features, it’s easy to share docs and send files—large or small—to family, friends, and co-workers through Dropbox’s cloud drive.

Features:
• Photo vault: automatically store videos, photos and docs from your camera roll to cloud photo storage, to backup your albums and for easy and secure video sharing and photo sharing.
• File organizer and manager: access any file or document in your account—even offline—and preview over 175 different file types with no special software required.
• Photo transfer app: send anywhere - easily transfer send large files and docs from your storage app by copying and pasting a link you can give to anyone, even if they don’t have a Dropbox account.
• Document Scanner: access an easy-to-use pdf scanner, and scan *documents using your mobile device and transform them into high-quality PDFs, so you can view, sign and send anywhere.
(*documents = receipts, IDs, photos, and more)
• Sync folders on your PC or Mac to Dropbox with cloud backup, and recover older versions or restore deleted files with version history and file recovery.

A cloud storage & drive app gives you extra space to backup, upload and share, scan and transfer files to the cloud, automatically. An easy backup and sync vault with safe access to your private or shared files. Today you can easily manage and share family albums, video albums and more.

Sign up now for your free Dropbox Plus trial. You’ll get 2 TB (2,000 GB) of storage space—that’s enough room to save files from all your linked devices. We’ve also introduced some new features as part of your Plus plan: Dropbox Passwords to store and sync passwords across all your devices and Dropbox Vault to secure and organize your most sensitive documents. And with Dropbox Rewind, you can roll back any file, folder, or your entire account, up to 30 days.

Existing Plus customers can upgrade to Dropbox Professional. With 3 TB (3,000GB), you can store all your stuff—from work projects to personal photos—and have space to spare. You and your clients can comment on most file types without leaving Dropbox. And you can protect your work with a watermark, add shared link controls, or rewind your account up to 180 days.

Before completing payment, you’ll see the plan price. This amount will be charged to your Google Play account and will vary by plan and country. Dropbox subscriptions purchased in app renew monthly or yearly, depending on your plan. To avoid auto-renewal, turn it off in at least 24 hours before your subscription renews. You can turn off auto-renewal anytime from your Google Play account settings.

Dropbox is a secure cloud solutions leader trusted by Fortune 500 companies for their most sensitive data. Over 14 million paid users choose Dropbox because they know they can count on a company that’s also dedicated to their security and privacy—no matter what they do or where they are. Let Dropbox be your all-in-one file storage, file organizer, file transfer, and file sharing solution for all your devices—from Android to iPhone and Mac to PC.

Dropbox is not affiliated with Amazon, Apple, Samsung, iCloud or Microsoft OneDrive.


We’d love to hear from you! Join the Dropbox community: https://www.dropboxforum.com

descriptionHtml:
Dropbox vous permet de télécharger, d’enregistrer et transférer des photos et des fichiers dans le cloud. Sauvegardez et synchronisez vos photos, vidéos, documents et autres fichiers sur le stockage en ligne et accédez-y depuis n’importe quel appareil, n’importe où. Grâce aux fonctions de partage avancées, partagez et envoyez facilement des photos ou des fichiers à votre famille, vos amis et vos collègues.

Fonctions :
• Téléchargez automatiquement des photos et des images enregistrées sur votre appareil photo vers l’espace de stockage en ligne pour partager facilement des photos et les envoyer n’importe où.
• Accédez à tous vos fichiers sur votre compte, même hors connexion, et affichez un aperçu pour 175 types de fichier sans aucun logiciel.
• Application de transfert de photos : enregistrez facilement des photos vers le cloud ou transférez-les depuis votre application de stockage en ligne.
• Numérisez des documents, des reçus, des documents d’identité, des photos et bien plus avec votre appareil mobile et transformez-les en fichiers PDF de haute qualité, afin de pouvoir les voir et les envoyer n’importe où.
• Synchronisez des dossiers sur votre ordinateur Windows ou Mac vers Dropbox avec la sauvegarde de votre ordinateur et récupérez des versions plus anciennes ou restaurez des fichiers supprimés avec l’historique des versions et la récupération des fichiers.

Le stockage en ligne et le stockage de photos sur lecteur vous permet de disposer d’un espace supplémentaire pour sauvegarder, télécharger, partager, numériser et transférer des photos ou des fichiers sur le cloud pour vous ! Un coffre-fort de données et une sauvegarde facile avec un accès sécurisé à vos fichiers privés ou partagés. Vous pouvez maintenant gérer et partager facilement des albums de famille, des albums vidéo et bien plus.

Abonnez-vous maintenant pour bénéficier d’un essai gratuit pour Dropbox Plus. Obtenez 2 To (2 000 Go) d’espace de stockage !

Nouvelles fonctions comprises dans le forfait Plus :
Dropbox Passwords : stockez et synchronisez les mots de passe sur tous vos appareils
Dropbox Vault : sécurisez vos documents et vos photos les plus sensibles
Dropbox Rewind : remontez dans le temps et restaurez un fichier, un dossier ou l’intégralité de votre compte à une date antérieure jusqu’à 30 jours

Passez sur Dropbox Professional - Obtenez 2 To (3 000 Go) d’espace de stockage ! Vous pouvez stocker toutes vos photos et vos fichiers avec un espace supplémentaire. Vos clients et vous peuvent commenter les fichiers sans quitter Dropbox. Protégez votre travail avec un filigrane, ajoutez des contrôles par lien partagé ou restaurez votre compte à une date antérieure jusqu’à 180 jours.

Avant d’effectuer le paiement, vous verrez le prix du forfait. Ce montant sera prélevé sur votre compte Google Play et variera selon le forfait souscrit et le pays. Les abonnements à Dropbox achetés dans l’application sont renouvelés chaque mois ou chaque année, selon votre forfait. Pour éviter le renouvellement automatique, désactivez-le pendant au moins 24 heures avant la date de renouvellement de votre abonnement. Vous pouvez désactiver le renouvellement automatique à tout instant dans les paramètres de votre compte Google Play.

Dropbox est un leader des solutions informatiques en nuage et en disque sécurisées et utilisées par des entreprises du classement Fortune 500 pour leurs données les plus sensibles. Plus de 14 millions d’abonnés choisissent Dropbox car ils savent qu’ils peuvent compter sur une entreprise qui garantit leur sécurité et leur confidentialité, quoi qu’ils fassent et où qu’ils se trouvent.

Dropbox n’est pas affilié à Google, Amazon, Apple, Samsung, iCloud ou Microsoft OneDrive.


Nous attendons de vos nouvelles ! Rejoignez la communauté Dropbox : https://www.dropboxforum.com
Conditions d’utilisation du service : https://www.dropbox.com/terms
Politique de confidentialité : https://www.dropbox.com/privacy

descriptionHtml:
Dropbox keeps your files organized, safe, and accessible at all times! You can effortlessly view and share files with anybody, no matter how big or small, by simply sending a link. Keep all of your important files in one place and easily backup your phone or computer. You can even use Dropbox to scan your files with ease and organize them in a safe storage.

Features:
• Photo vault: automatically store videos, photos and docs from your camera roll to cloud photo storage, to backup your albums and for easy and secure video sharing and photo sharing.
• File organizer and manager: access any file or document in your account—even offline—and preview over 175 different file types with no special software required.
• Photo transfer app: send anywhere - easily transfer send large files and docs from your storage app by copying and pasting a link you can give to anyone, even if they don’t have a Dropbox account.
• Document Scanner: access an easy-to-use pdf scanner, and scan *documents using your mobile device and transform them into high-quality PDFs, so you can view, sign and send anywhere.
(*documents = receipts, IDs, photos, and more)
• Sync folders on your PC or Mac to Dropbox with cloud backup, and recover older versions or restore deleted files with version history and file recovery.

A cloud storage & drive app gives you extra space to backup, upload and share, scan and transfer files to the cloud, automatically. An easy backup and sync vault with safe access to your private or shared files. Today you can easily manage and share family albums, video albums and more.

Sign up now for your free Dropbox Plus trial. You’ll get 2 TB (2,000 GB) of storage space—that’s enough room to save files from all your linked devices. We’ve also introduced some new features as part of your Plus plan: Dropbox Passwords to store and sync passwords across all your devices and Dropbox Vault to secure and organize your most sensitive documents. And with Dropbox Rewind, you can roll back any file, folder, or your entire account, up to 30 days.

Existing Plus customers can upgrade to Dropbox Professional. With 3 TB (3,000GB), you can store all your stuff—from work projects to personal photos—and have space to spare. You and your clients can comment on most file types without leaving Dropbox. And you can protect your work with a watermark, add shared link controls, or rewind your account up to 180 days.

Before completing payment, you’ll see the plan price. This amount will be charged to your Google Play account and will vary by plan and country. Dropbox subscriptions purchased in app renew monthly or yearly, depending on your plan. To avoid auto-renewal, turn it off in at least 24 hours before your subscription renews. You can turn off auto-renewal anytime from your Google Play account settings.

Dropbox is a secure cloud solutions leader trusted by Fortune 500 companies for their most sensitive data. Over 14 million paid users choose Dropbox because they know they can count on a company that’s also dedicated to their security and privacy—no matter what they do or where they are. Let Dropbox be your all-in-one file storage, file organizer, file transfer, and file sharing solution for all your devices—from Android to iPhone and Mac to PC.

Dropbox is not affiliated with Amazon, Apple, Samsung, iCloud or Microsoft OneDrive.


We’d love to hear from you! Join the Dropbox community: https://www.dropboxforum.com

creator: Dropbox, Inc.
descriptionHtml:
Dropbox vous permet de télécharger, d’enregistrer et transférer des photos et des fichiers dans le cloud. Sauvegardez et synchronisez vos photos, vidéos, documents et autres fichiers sur le stockage en ligne et accédez-y depuis n’importe quel appareil, n’importe où. Grâce aux fonctions de partage avancées, partagez et envoyez facilement des photos ou des fichiers à votre famille, vos amis et vos collègues.

Fonctions :
• Téléchargez automatiquement des photos et des images enregistrées sur votre appareil photo vers l’espace de stockage en ligne pour partager facilement des photos et les envoyer n’importe où.
• Accédez à tous vos fichiers sur votre compte, même hors connexion, et affichez un aperçu pour 175 types de fichier sans aucun logiciel.
• Application de transfert de photos : enregistrez facilement des photos vers le cloud ou transférez-les depuis votre application de stockage en ligne.
• Numérisez des documents, des reçus, des documents d’identité, des photos et bien plus avec votre appareil mobile et transformez-les en fichiers PDF de haute qualité, afin de pouvoir les voir et les envoyer n’importe où.
• Synchronisez des dossiers sur votre ordinateur Windows ou Mac vers Dropbox avec la sauvegarde de votre ordinateur et récupérez des versions plus anciennes ou restaurez des fichiers supprimés avec l’historique des versions et la récupération des fichiers.

Le stockage en ligne et le stockage de photos sur lecteur vous permet de disposer d’un espace supplémentaire pour sauvegarder, télécharger, partager, numériser et transférer des photos ou des fichiers sur le cloud pour vous ! Un coffre-fort de données et une sauvegarde facile avec un accès sécurisé à vos fichiers privés ou partagés. Vous pouvez maintenant gérer et partager facilement des albums de famille, des albums vidéo et bien plus.

Abonnez-vous maintenant pour bénéficier d’un essai gratuit pour Dropbox Plus. Obtenez 2 To (2 000 Go) d’espace de stockage !

Nouvelles fonctions comprises dans le forfait Plus :
Dropbox Passwords : stockez et synchronisez les mots de passe sur tous vos appareils
Dropbox Vault : sécurisez vos documents et vos photos les plus sensibles
Dropbox Rewind : remontez dans le temps et restaurez un fichier, un dossier ou l’intégralité de votre compte à une date antérieure jusqu’à 30 jours

Passez sur Dropbox Professional - Obtenez 2 To (3 000 Go) d’espace de stockage ! Vous pouvez stocker toutes vos photos et vos fichiers avec un espace supplémentaire. Vos clients et vous peuvent commenter les fichiers sans quitter Dropbox. Protégez votre travail avec un filigrane, ajoutez des contrôles par lien partagé ou restaurez votre compte à une date antérieure jusqu’à 180 jours.

Avant d’effectuer le paiement, vous verrez le prix du forfait. Ce montant sera prélevé sur votre compte Google Play et variera selon le forfait souscrit et le pays. Les abonnements à Dropbox achetés dans l’application sont renouvelés chaque mois ou chaque année, selon votre forfait. Pour éviter le renouvellement automatique, désactivez-le pendant au moins 24 heures avant la date de renouvellement de votre abonnement. Vous pouvez désactiver le renouvellement automatique à tout instant dans les paramètres de votre compte Google Play.

Dropbox est un leader des solutions informatiques en nuage et en disque sécurisées et utilisées par des entreprises du classement Fortune 500 pour leurs données les plus sensibles. Plus de 14 millions d’abonnés choisissent Dropbox car ils savent qu’ils peuvent compter sur une entreprise qui garantit leur sécurité et leur confidentialité, quoi qu’ils fassent et où qu’ils se trouvent.

Dropbox n’est pas affilié à Google, Amazon, Apple, Samsung, iCloud ou Microsoft OneDrive.


Nous attendons de vos nouvelles ! Rejoignez la communauté Dropbox : https://www.dropboxforum.com
Conditions d’utilisation du service : https://www.dropbox.com/terms
Politique de confidentialité : https://www.dropbox.com/privacy

And with advanced sharing features, it’s easy to share docs and send files—large or small—to family, friends, and co-workers through Dropbox’s cloud drive.

Features:
• Photo vault - automatically store videos , photos and docs from your camera roll to cloud photo storage, to backup your albums and for easy and secure video sharing and photo sharing.
• File organizer and manager - access any file or document in your account—even offline—and preview over 175 different file types with no special software required.
• Photo transfer app: send anywhere - easily transfer send large files and docs from your storage app by copying and pasting a link you can give to anyone, even if they don’t have a Dropbox account.
• Document Scanner - access an easy-to-use pdf scanner, and scan *documents using your mobile device and transform them into high-quality PDFs, so you can view, sign and send anywhere.
(*documents = receipts, IDs, photos, and more)
• Sync folders on your PC or Mac to Dropbox with cloud backup, and recover older versions or restore deleted files with version history and file recovery.

A cloud storage & drive app gives you extra space to backup, upload and share, scan and transfer files to the cloud, automatically. An easy backup and sync vault with safe access to your private or shared files. Today you can easily manage and share family albums, video albums and more.

Sign up now for your free Dropbox Plus trial. You’ll get 2 TB (2,000 GB) of storage space—that’s enough room to save files from all your linked devices. We’ve also introduced some new features as part of your Plus plan: Dropbox Passwords to store and sync passwords across all your devices and Dropbox Vault to secure and organize your most sensitive documents. And with Dropbox Rewind, you can roll back any file, folder, or your entire account, up to 30 days.

Existing Plus customers can upgrade to Dropbox Professional. With 3 TB (3,000GB), you can store all your stuff—from work projects to personal photos—and have space to spare. You and your clients can comment on most file types without leaving Dropbox. And you can protect your work with a watermark, add shared link controls, or rewind your account up to 180 days.

Before completing payment, you’ll see the plan price. This amount will be charged to your Google Play account and will vary by plan and country. Dropbox subscriptions purchased in app renew monthly or yearly, depending on your plan. To avoid auto-renewal, turn it off in at least 24 hours before your subscription renews. You can turn off auto-renewal anytime from your Google Play account settings.

Dropbox is a secure cloud solutions leader trusted by Fortune 500 companies for their most sensitive data. Over 14 million paid users choose Dropbox because they know they can count on a company that’s also dedicated to their security and privacy—no matter what they do or where they are. Let Dropbox be your all-in-one file storage, file organizer, file transfer, and file sharing solution for all your devices—from Android to iPhone and Mac to PC.

Dropbox is not affiliated with Amazon, Apple, Samsung, iCloud or Microsoft OneDrive.

creator: Dropbox, Inc.
descriptionHtml:
Dropbox vous permet de télécharger, d’enregistrer et transférer des photos et des fichiers dans le cloud. Sauvegardez et synchronisez vos photos, vidéos, documents et autres fichiers sur le stockage en ligne et accédez-y depuis n’importe quel appareil, n’importe où. Grâce aux fonctions de partage avancées, partagez et envoyez facilement des photos ou des fichiers à votre famille, vos amis et vos collègues.

Fonctions :
• Téléchargez automatiquement des photos et des images enregistrées sur votre appareil photo vers l’espace de stockage en ligne pour partager facilement des photos et les envoyer n’importe où.
• Accédez à tous vos fichiers sur votre compte, même hors connexion, et affichez un aperçu pour 175 types de fichier sans aucun logiciel.
• Application de transfert de photos : enregistrez facilement des photos vers le cloud ou transférez-les depuis votre application de stockage en ligne.
• Numérisez des documents, des reçus, des documents d’identité, des photos et bien plus avec votre appareil mobile et transformez-les en fichiers PDF de haute qualité, afin de pouvoir les voir et les envoyer n’importe où.
• Synchronisez des dossiers sur votre ordinateur Windows ou Mac vers Dropbox avec la sauvegarde de votre ordinateur et récupérez des versions plus anciennes ou restaurez des fichiers supprimés avec l’historique des versions et la récupération des fichiers.

Le stockage en ligne et le stockage de photos sur lecteur vous permet de disposer d’un espace supplémentaire pour sauvegarder, télécharger, partager, numériser et transférer des photos ou des fichiers sur le cloud pour vous ! Un coffre-fort de données et une sauvegarde facile avec un accès sécurisé à vos fichiers privés ou partagés. Vous pouvez maintenant gérer et partager facilement des albums de famille, des albums vidéo et bien plus.

Abonnez-vous maintenant pour bénéficier d’un essai gratuit pour Dropbox Plus. Obtenez 2 To (2 000 Go) d’espace de stockage !

Nouvelles fonctions comprises dans le forfait Plus :
Dropbox Passwords : stockez et synchronisez les mots de passe sur tous vos appareils
Dropbox Vault : sécurisez vos documents et vos photos les plus sensibles
Dropbox Rewind : remontez dans le temps et restaurez un fichier, un dossier ou l’intégralité de votre compte à une date antérieure jusqu’à 30 jours

Passez sur Dropbox Professional - Obtenez 2 To (3 000 Go) d’espace de stockage ! Vous pouvez stocker toutes vos photos et vos fichiers avec un espace supplémentaire. Vos clients et vous peuvent commenter les fichiers sans quitter Dropbox. Protégez votre travail avec un filigrane, ajoutez des contrôles par lien partagé ou restaurez votre compte à une date antérieure jusqu’à 180 jours.

Avant d’effectuer le paiement, vous verrez le prix du forfait. Ce montant sera prélevé sur votre compte Google Play et variera selon le forfait souscrit et le pays. Les abonnements à Dropbox achetés dans l’application sont renouvelés chaque mois ou chaque année, selon votre forfait. Pour éviter le renouvellement automatique, désactivez-le pendant au moins 24 heures avant la date de renouvellement de votre abonnement. Vous pouvez désactiver le renouvellement automatique à tout instant dans les paramètres de votre compte Google Play.

Dropbox est un leader des solutions informatiques en nuage et en disque sécurisées et utilisées par des entreprises du classement Fortune 500 pour leurs données les plus sensibles. Plus de 14 millions d’abonnés choisissent Dropbox car ils savent qu’ils peuvent compter sur une entreprise qui garantit leur sécurité et leur confidentialité, quoi qu’ils fassent et où qu’ils se trouvent.

Dropbox n’est pas affilié à Google, Amazon, Apple, Samsung, iCloud ou Microsoft OneDrive.


Nous attendons de vos nouvelles ! Rejoignez la communauté Dropbox : https://www.dropboxforum.com
Conditions d’utilisation du service : https://www.dropbox.com/terms
Politique de confidentialité : https://www.dropbox.com/privacy

Features:
• Photo vault: automatically store videos, photos and docs from your camera roll to cloud photo storage, to backup your albums and for easy and secure video sharing and photo sharing.
• File organizer and manager: access any file or document in your account—even offline—and preview over 175 different file types with no special software required.
• Photo transfer app: send anywhere - easily transfer send large files and docs from your storage app by copying and pasting a link you can give to anyone, even if they don’t have a Dropbox account.

(*documents = receipts, IDs, photos, and more)

Sign up now for your free Dropbox Plus trial. You’ll get 2 TB (2,000 GB) of storage space—that’s enough room to save files from all your linked devices. We’ve also introduced some new features as part of your Plus plan: Dropbox Passwords to store and sync passwords across all your devices and Dropbox Vault to secure and organize your most sensitive documents. And with Dropbox Rewind, you can roll back any file, folder, or your entire account, up to 30 days.

Existing Plus customers can upgrade to Dropbox Professional. With 3 TB (3,000GB), you can store all your stuff—from work projects to personal photos—and have space to spare. You and your clients can comment on most file types without leaving Dropbox. And you can protect your work with a watermark, add shared link controls, or rewind your account up to 180 days.
